a) True
b) True
c) False
d) False
e) False
f) True
g) True

The given if-else statements behave the same way. 
Statement 1 states that if karel can pick thing, he must turn right, and if he cannot pick something to turn left. 
Statement 2 states the exact same thing but in a different way. 
It says that if karel cannot pick thing to turn left, otherwise if he could pick thing to turn right.
Therefore the if-else statements behave the same way.
